data.meta_description: In MEMORY of JO VAN FLEET on her BIRTHDAY - Born Catherine Josephine Van Fleet, American stage, film, and TV actress. During her long career, which spanned over four decades, she often played characters much older than her actual age. Van Fleet won a Tony Award in 1954 for her performance in the Broadway production The Trip to Bountiful, and the next year she won an Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress for her supporting role in East of Eden. Dec 30, 1914 - Jun 10, 1996 (undisclosed)
